div><div class="right-4LP3J flex-aYeiI"><div class="profileIconDropdownContainer-DM-LM"><button type="button" class="profileIconLoggedOutBtn-F9aJJ"><span class="sr-only">Sign in</span><svg width="1em" height="1em" viewBox="0 0 472 472" fill="currentColor" role="img" aria-label="User" class="profileIconLoggedOutImg-UUxUk"><path d="M403 69a235 235 0 0 0-334 0 235 235 0 0 0 0 334 235 235 0 0 0 334 0 235 235 0 0 0 0-334ZM118 412a122 122 0 0 1 237 0 211 211 0 0 1-237 0Zm41-197a77 77 0 1 1 155 0 77 77 0 0 1-155 0Zm216 181c-14-43-48-77-91-92a101 101 0 1 0-96 0c-43 15-77 49-91 92a212 212 0 1 1 278 0Z"></path></svg></button></div></div></div></header><header class="header-XaCCp"><div class="headerArt--fFif"><img src="/static/assets/science-quickly-0ff8b63d.jpg" alt="" fetchpriority="high" loading="eager" role="presentation" aria-hidden="true"/></div><div class="headerContent-KJ7lS"><div class="coverArt-rjjdP"><img src="/static/assets/science-quickly-84ef5bda.jpg" alt="Cover art for Science, Quickly" fetchpriority="high" loading="eager"/></div><div class="info-XxDwT"><h1 class="title-jbuAx">Science, Quickly</h1><div class="description-35N4G">Leading science and tech journalists dive into a rich world of scientific discovery in this bite-size science variety show.</div><aside class="callout-sPVS7"><strong class="calloutTitle-i1DFh">Subscribe to listen</strong><ul class="calloutLinks-uCyde"><li><a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/science-quickly/id189330872?mt=2" title="Science, Quickly on Apple Podcasts" rel="noopener nofollow" target="_blank">Apple</a></li><li><a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/7uz2rjUW6bGrPCgw4rI8K4" title="Science, Quickly on Spotify" rel="noopener nofollow" target="_blank">Spotify</a></li><li><a href="https://www.scientificamerican.com/syndication/60secondscience.xml" title="Science, Quickly via RSS" rel="noopener nofollow" target="_blank">RSS</a></li></ul></aside></div></div></header><div class="articleList-R10iq root-fREBs podcastList-oAOZG"><div class="articleListGrid-N4wvY grid-PoVrj"><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/podcasts-of-the-year-cleo-the-mysterious-math-menace/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Mathematics</span> <!-- -->December 29, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Podcasts of the Year: Cleo, the Mysterious Math Menace</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>In 2013 a new user named Cleo took an online math forum by storm with unproved answers. Today she&rsquo;s an urban legend. But who was she? A 2023 editor's pick.&nbsp;</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Tulika Bose, Allison Parshall, Carin Leong</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM3301953839&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/talking-to-animals-with-artificial-intelligence/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Artificial Intelligence</span> <!-- -->December 27, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Podcasts of the Year: Talking to Animals with Artificial Intelligence</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p><strong id="docs-internal-guid-15643de0-7fff-32a7-e143-ebaa42bbfb07">Advanced sensors and artificial intelligence could have us at the brink of interspecies communication</strong></p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Kelso Harper, Sophie Bushwick</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM2452233997&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/how-to-avoid-holiday-hangovers/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Diet</span> <!-- -->December 22, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">How to Avoid Holiday Hangovers</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>The holidays are a time for indulgence, but there are ways to drink alcohol without suffering the painful effects.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Josh Fischman, Tanya Lewis, Alexa Lim</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM1864205259&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><div class="ad-placeholder ad-I2Hlv fullRow--PD0c"><div class="breakoutContainer-8fsaw"><gpt-ad class="ad-G8iDN" unitpath="injector" sizes-from-0="300x250,300x50,320x50,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-745="728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-1000="970x250,970x90,728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2"></gpt-ad></div></div><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/what-better-gift-for-the-holidays-than-a-monstrous-mystery/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Evolution</span> <!-- -->December 20, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">What Better Gift for the Holidays Than a Monstrous Mystery?</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>We&rsquo;re looking back at 2023 for our favorite podcast shows and one about the largest bird to ever fly the skies just flew to the top of the list.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Jeffery DelViscio, Flora Lichtman</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM4442759499&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/are-orca-whales-friends-or-foes/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Animals</span> <!-- -->December 18, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Are Orcas Friends or Foes?</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>The stories we tell about orcas might say more about us than about them</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Carin Leong</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM5491244488&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/turns-out-undersea-kelp-forests-are-crucial-to-salmon/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Ecology</span> <!-- -->December 15, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Turns Out Undersea Kelp Forests Are Crucial to Salmon</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>The beloved fish that feed orcas and humans depend on kelp forests&rsquo; unique habitat.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Starre Vartan</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM9880177316&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><div class="ad-placeholder ad-I2Hlv fullRow--PD0c"><div class="breakoutContainer-8fsaw"><gpt-ad class="ad-G8iDN" unitpath="injector" sizes-from-0="300x250,300x50,320x50,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-745="728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-1000="970x250,970x90,728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2"></gpt-ad></div></div><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/researchers-just-created-the-worlds-first-permafrost-atlas-of-the-entire-arctic/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Climate Change</span> <!-- -->December 13, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Researchers Just Created the World's First Permafrost Atlas of the Entire Arctic</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>The Arctic Permafrost Atlas, which took years to create, is both beautiful and sobering, given the pace of climate change.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Emily Schwing</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM2434593821&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/a-new-type-of-heart-disease-is-on-the-rise1/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Health Care</span> <!-- -->December 11, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">A New Type of Heart Disease is on the Rise</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>Problems with the heart, kidneys and metabolic health are all connected</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Josh Fischman, Tanya Lewis, Elah Feder</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM4803149826&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/ai-can-now-read-your-cats-pain1/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Artificial Intelligence</span> <!-- -->December 8, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">AI Can Now Read Your Cat&rsquo;s Pain</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>Thanks to researchers, new AI tech is delving into feline feelings to see when cats could need medical help.&nbsp;</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Tulika Bose, Sophie Bushwick</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM8090771579&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><div class="ad-placeholder ad-I2Hlv fullRow--PD0c"><div class="breakoutContainer-8fsaw"><gpt-ad class="ad-G8iDN" unitpath="injector" sizes-from-0="300x250,300x50,320x50,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-745="728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2" sizes-from-1000="970x250,970x90,728x90,300x250,fluid,2x2"></gpt-ad></div></div><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/these-researchers-put-sperm-through-a-kind-of-hunger-games1/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Physiology</span> <!-- -->December 6, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">These Researchers Put Sperm Through a Kind of &lsquo;Hunger Games&rsquo;</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>The research focused on&nbsp;figuring out what&nbsp;enables certain sperm to&nbsp;gain some competitive advantage over millions of others fighting for the same prize.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Karen Hopkin</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM1205182223&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/is-too-little-play-hurting-our-kids/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Mental Health</span> <!-- -->December 4, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">Is Too Little Play Hurting Our Kids?</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>A long-term decline in unsupervised activity may be contributing to mental health declines in children and adolescents.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Joseph Polidoro</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM6043701982&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article><article class="article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX article-pFLe7 item-NF5qX"><a class="articleLink-2OMNo" href="/podcast/episode/how-misinformation-spreads-through-conflict/" data-testid="article-link"><div class="meta-RJMPT"><span class="metaCategory-l96EY">Politics</span> <!-- -->December 1, 2023</div><h2 class="articleTitle-mtY5p">How Misinformation Spreads through Conflict</h2></a><section><div class="dek-KweYs"><p>Three&nbsp;experts break down how misinformation and propaganda spread through conflict and how to debunk it yourself.</p></div><p class="authors-NCGt1">Tulika Bose, Sophie Bushwick</p></section><div class="articleMedia-5BcQK"><a name="playerAnchor" id="playerAnchor"></a><iframe frameBorder="0" height="200" scrolling="no" loading="lazy" src="https://playlist.megaphone.fm/?e=SAM8388797267&amp;light=true&amp;artwork=false" width="100%"></iframe></div></article></div></div><div class="paginationContainer-Dir8D"><a class="paginationButton-Q-Ffv" href="?page=2">Next</a></div><footer class="footer-VfsmT"><div class="footerContainer-pfbjC"><h2 class="footerMainText-wQ3og">Expand Your World with Science</h2></div><div class="footerFlexContainer-XKe5g footerContainer-pfbjC"><div class="fo